==Latin==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[πρόγνωσις]]''' (''prognosis'') "foreknowledge, perceiving beforehand, prediction", from prefix '''[[προ-]]''' (''[[pro-]]'') + '''[[γνώσις]]''' (''gnosis'') " seeking to know, inquiry, investigation, a knowing, knowledge", from '''[[γιγνώσκω]]''' (''gignosko'') "to learn to know, to perceive, to mark, to learn". 
===Noun===
'''prognōsis, [[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|-ōsis]]''' ''f''

#[[forecast]], [[prediction]]

